criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Pathologically diagnosed as epithelial ovarian cancer, fallopian tube cancer, stage
             II-IV period, the expected survival of> 6 months;

          -  ECOG <2;

          -  Liver and kidney function is normal;

          -  No uncontrollable high blood pressure, bleeding, perforation, obstruction.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Serious cardiopulmonary insufficiency, can not tolerate chemotherapy;

          -  Pregnant or lactating women;

          -  3 years have occurred in other tumors (cervical cancer in situ, has cured basal cell
             carcinoma, except for bladder epithelial tumors);

          -  Allergic to apatinib or its accessories.
